-- American Apparel hires turnaround expert as interim CEO 
-- By Sruthi Ramakrishnan in Bangalore
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 09:01AM EDT
-- None



Sept 29 (Reuters) - American Apparel Inc <APP.A> said it hired Scott Brubaker, a managing director at turnaround firm Alvarez & Marsal, as interim chief executive, three months after ousting its CEO and founder Dov Charney.

The company also named Hassan Natha, a former Nike Inc <NKE.N> executive, as chief financial officer. [ID:nPn6tThhz] American Apparel fired Charney in June, citing alleged misuse of corporate funds and his role in disseminating nude photos of an ex-employee who had sued him. [ID:nL4N0P00U3]